gomodel:SYNGO_3813  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"NRG1 and its receptors ErbB2 and ErbB4 are associated with cholinergic C-bouton afferents on ventral horn MNs.\"\n\nFig.4: \"Ultrastructural immunolocalization of NRG1 at C-type synapses on spinal cord MNs\"\n- \"All procedures gave the same result, showing an exquisite localization of NRG1 within the postsynaptic subsurface cistern in association with MN C termini (Fig. 4A-E). \". Experimental description: Fig.1: \" NRG1-immunopositive spots decorated the soma and proximal dendrites of large MNs at a density of 16.20 ± 2.18/100 μm of somatic perimeter (n=67 somata from P90 mice). \"\nFig.4: \"To determine the subcellular localization of NRG1 in MN central synapses, high-resolution immunoelectron microcopy was performed in samples of adult mouse spinal cord \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-27" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3813" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

